{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_018oz9YFFX7qxULPWesCNYQk","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"All verification criteria are satisfied:\n\n| Check | Result |\n|-------|--------|\n| Cluster health | **green**, 5 nodes |\n| `app-data` shards on new nodes | Both on `es-data-0` and `es-data-1` (outside original 3) |\n| Zone attributes differ | `es-cluster-{0,1,2}` → `zone=original`; `es-data-{0,1}` → `zone=new` |\n| `es-cluster` StatefulSet replicas | Still **3** (unchanged) |\n\n**What was done:**\n1. Updated `es-config` ConfigMap to add `node.attr.zone: original`, then rolling-restarted the `es-cluster` StatefulSet — cluster stayed green throughout.\n2. Created `es-data-config` ConfigMap with `zone: new` and data-only node roles (`[data, ingest]`, no master).\n3. Created headless Service `es-data` and a separate `es-data` StatefulSet (2 replicas) that joins the existing cluster via `discovery.seed_hosts` pointing at the original 3 masters.\n4. Applied `index.routing.allocation.require.zone: new` on the `app-data` index — Elasticsearch immediately relocated both shards to the new nodes."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1244,"cache_read_input_tokens":48360,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1244},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"8f884086-d68f-4105-8f55-b209ed35e740","uuid":"5d09e6e7-3ded-479b-b691-991766c67686","request_id":"req_011CcM4pFutDKZh4nktpn2GK"}
